on making it the worlds second largest metropolitan area other major cities include busan  million incheon  million daegu  million daejeon  million gwangju  million and ulsan  million the population has also been shaped by international migration after world war ii and the division of the korean peninsula about four million people from north korea crossed the border to south korea this trend of net entry reversed over the next  years because of emigration especially to the united states and canada south koreas total population in  was  million and has more than doubled to  million by  south korea is one of the most ethnically homogeneous societies in the world with more than  of inhabitants having korean ethnicity the percentage of foreign nationals has been growing rapidly as of update south korea had  foreign residents  of the population however more than half of them are ethnic koreans with a foreign citizenship for example migrants from china prc make up  of foreign nationals but approximately  of the chinese citizens in korea are joseonjok 조선족 in korean prc citizens of korean ethnicity regardless of the ethnicity there are  us military personnel serving in south korea most serving a oneyear unaccompanied tour though approximately  serve longer tours accompanied by family according to the korea national statistical office in addition about  english teachers from englishspeaking countries reside temporarily in korea currently south korea has one of the highest rates of growth of foreign born population with about  foreign born residents obtaining south korean citizenship every year since  south koreas birthrate was the worlds lowest in  if this continues its population is expected to decrease by  to  million in  south koreas annual birthrate is approximately  births per  people however the birthrate has increased by  in  and korea no longer has the worlds lowest birthrate according to a  report from the chosun ilbo south koreas total fertility rate  children born