to china proper yang ti continued to send his armies against koguryŏ but again without success and before long his warweakened empire crumbled   nahm andrew c  a panorama of  years korean history second revised ed seoul hollym international corporation p  isbn x china which had been split into many states since the early rd century was reunified by the sui dynasty at the end of the th century soon after that sui china mobilized a large number of troops and launched war against koguryŏ however the people of koguryŏ were united and they were able to repel the chinese aggressors in  sui troops invaded korea again but koguryŏ forces fought bravely and destroyed sui troops everywhere general ŭlchi mundŏk of koguryŏ completely wiped out some  sui troops which came across the yalu river in the battles near the salsu river now chŏngchŏn river with his ingenious military tactics only  sui troops were able to flee from korea the sui dynasty which wasted so much energy and manpower in aggressive wars against koguryŏ fell in    ebrey patricia buckley walthall anne palais james b east asia a cultural social and political history houghton mifflin p  isbn  retrieved september     kitagawa joseph the religious traditions of asia religion history and culture routledge p  isbn  retrieved july     ebrey patricia buckley walthall anne palais james b east asia a cultural social and political history volume i to  cengage learning p  isbn  retrieved september     a brief history of korea ewha womans university press pp – isbn  retrieved november     yu chaishin the new history of korean civilization iuniverse p  isbn  retrieved november     kim jinwung a history of korea from land of the morning calm to states in conflict indiana university press pp – isbn  retrieved september     wells kenneth m korea outline of a civilisation brill pp – isbn  retrieved september     injae lee miller owen jinhoon park hyunhae yi korean history in maps cambridge university press pp – isbn  retrieved febru