ryŏ descent fled to koryŏ wang kŏn warmly welcomed them and generously gave them land along with bestowing the name wang kye successor of the royal wang on the parhae crown prince tae kwanghyŏn wang kŏn entered his name in the royal household register thus clearly conveying the idea that they belonged to the same lineage and also had rituals performed in honor of his progenitor thus koryŏ achieved a true national unification that embraced not only the later three kingdoms but even survivors of koguryŏ lineage from the parhae kingdom   world treasures beginnings library of congress archived from the original on august   retrieved july     digital jikji digital jikji archived from the original on march   retrieved april     bulliet richard crossley pamela headrick daniel hirsch steven johnson lyman the earth and its peoples brief a global history cengage learning p  isbn  retrieved september     cohen warren i east asia at the center four thousand years of engagement with the world columbia university press p  isbn  retrieved september     lee kenneth b korea and east asia the story of a phoenix greenwood publishing group p  isbn  retrieved july     bowman john columbia chronologies of asian history and culture columbia university press p  isbn  retrieved august     a b lee kenneth b korea and east asia the story of a phoenix greenwood publishing group p  isbn  retrieved november     currie lorenzo through the eyes of the pack xlibris corporation p  isbn  retrieved july     yi kibaek a new history of korea harvard university press p  isbn  retrieved november     selin helaine encyclopaedia of the history of science technology and medicine in nonwesten cultures springer science  business media pp – isbn  retrieved july     haralambous yannis horne p scott fonts  encodings oreilly media inc p  isbn  retrieved november     lee kenneth b korea and east asia the story of a phoenix greenwood publishing group p  isbn  retrieved july     turnbull stephen november   the samura